Current Patch Set: 1&lt;br/&gt;
Commit: e0695b637113b823987ca0d2024731f52df1ba14&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="410059" author="adilger" created="Thu, 4 Apr 2024 19:39:56 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Sebastien, do you have any thoughts on how difficult this would be to implement?  It would add a new 64-bit capability mask to the nodemap config, which would be used in preference to the global &lt;tt&gt;enable_cap_mask&lt;/tt&gt; parameter if it is set.  We might consider a separate RBAC flag that indicates if the capability mask is a &quot;set&quot; or a &quot;mask&quot; on the client, so that it is possible to add capabilities (for a small number of admin or protocol export nodes) or reduce them (for e.g. remote data transfer nodes, or similar)?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
